text.section:
A permit is not required under this section to erect or maintain any outdoor sign:
That is used only to advertise the sale or lease of the property on which it is located;
That is on or within 100 feet of any building or the entrance to any building in which the business advertised is carried on;
That is used only to advertise:
A Maryland historic shrine or institution; or
A county or church fair held in this State;
That advertises a candidate or the support or defeat of any proposition. This sign:
Shall comply with all provisions of the Election Law Article;
Shall comply with public safety requirements as set forth in § 8-716 of this subtitle;
Shall conform to all local restrictions and zoning requirements which are more restrictive than this section; and
Shall conform to the restrictions and requirements of Parts IV and V of this subtitle; or
That is only a temporary outdoor sign that advertises the sale in season of fresh produce on property that adjoins a State highway by a person who has grown the fresh produce and who owns, rents, or has permission to sell on the property. This sign:
Shall comply with public safety requirements as set forth in § 8-716 of this subtitle;
Shall conform to all local restrictions and zoning requirements that are more restrictive than this section, including any applicable time limitation;
Shall conform to the restrictions and requirements of Parts IV and V of this subtitle; and
Shall be removed or covered when produce is no longer for sale.
